                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": "1"
                },
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The golem fills an empty vial from one of its alchemical chambers to create a bomb and then makes a bomb @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.Strike]{Strike}. Determine the type of bomb created by rolling [[/r 1d6]] on the alchemical chambers list above. On a roll of 1-4, it creates the corresponding greater alchemical bomb: an @Compendium[pf2e.equipment-srd.Acid Flask (Greater)]{Acid Flask (Greater)} from chamber 1, a @Compendium[pf2e.equipment-srd.Frost Vial (Greater)]{Frost Vial (Greater)} from chamber 2, @Compendium[pf2e.equipment-srd.Bottled Lightning (Greater)]{Bottled Lightning (Greater)} from chamber 3, or @Compendium[pf2e.equipment-srd.Alchemist's Fire (Greater)]{Alchemist's Fire (Greater)} from chamber 4. On a roll of 5, it creates a poisonous bomb that deals [[/r 3d10 # poison]] poison damage and [[/r 3 # poison splash]]{3 poison splash damage} with no other effects. On a roll of 6, it creates a sickness bomb, which exposes the target and all creatures in the splash radius to the @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Sickened]{Sickened} effect; creatures hit by only the splash receive a +2 circumstance bonus to their Fortitude saves.</p>"
